"What we need to understand better as a nation is that our infrastructure does not just look like steel, concrete and transport – it is also the nurturing, patience and diligence of care workers. text:
Before the #pandemic, some of you had to cut back on the amount of food on your table and the medicine in your cupboards just to keep a roof over your heads. You've worked hard all your life. These types of decisions shouldn’t weigh heavy on your hearts.

NCOA’s Boost Your Budget® Week encourages seniors to find the resources they need to pay for daily living expenses, such as food, prescriptions, rent, utilities, and more. Learn more about our screening tool that only takes a few minutes—is free, confidential, and there’s no sign-up or registration required.
https://bit.ly/3a3jsGQ
#BoostYourBudget #BoostYourBudgetWeek #AgingWellMatters

text:
From 2019 to 2029, the long-term care sector will need to fill 7.4 million total direct care job openings, including 1.3 million new jobs and an additional 6.2 million job openings as workers leave the field for a new occupation or leave the labor force altogether.

Our new research examines the outlook on the direct care workforce, including how the COVID-19 pandemic has impacted future demand for these workers.

PHINATIONAL.ORG
Will COVID-19 Change Direct Care Employment? New Data Offer Clues.
